## Token Usage

### Color

**container** — Container background, border, and surface colors
- `--color-container-background-accent`
- `--color-container-background-accent-active`
- `--color-container-background-accent-focus`

### Space

**container** — Container padding and internal spacing
- `--space-container-padding-large`
- `--space-container-padding-medium`
- `--space-container-padding-small`

### Radius

**radius** — Border radius for container corners
- `--radius-0`
- `--radius-10`
- `--radius-20`

## Usage Patterns

### Container

```tsx
() => {
  return (
    <div style={{ width: '100%', height: '500px' }}>
      <p>Skeleton for container with flex width</p>
      <SkeletonContainer />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Skeleton For Icon

```tsx
() => {
  return (
    <div>
      <p>X small icon</p>
      <SkeletonIcon size="xsmall" />

      <p>Small icon</p>
      <SkeletonIcon size="small" />

      <p>Medium icon</p>
      <SkeletonIcon size="medium" />

      <p>Large icon</p>
      <SkeletonIcon size="large" />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Skeleton For Action And Input

```tsx
() => {
  return (
    <div>
      <p>Small action / input</p>
      <SkeletonAction size="small" />

      <p>Medium action / input</p>
      <SkeletonAction size="medium" />

      <p>Large action / input</p>
      <SkeletonAction size="large" />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Skeleton For Text

```tsx
(args: {
  numberOfLines: number;
  spacing: number;
}) => {
  const [lines, setLines] = useState(1);

  useEffect(() => {
    setLines(args.numberOfLines);
  }, [args.numberOfLines]);

  return (
    <div>
      <p>Text skeleton with flex width and multiple lines</p>
      <SkeletonText spacing={args.spacing} numberOfLines={lines} />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Skeleton For Chip

```tsx
() => {
  return (
    <div>
      <p>
        The chip configuration has a full radius, fixed height, and flexible
        width.
      </p>
      <p>Chip may be used for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Chips</li>
        <li>Intuit Assist access point</li>
      </ul>
      <SkeletonChip />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Showcase

```tsx
() => {
  return (
    <div className={styles.showcase}>
      Action Skeleton
      <SkeletonAction size="medium" />
      Chip Skeleton
      <SkeletonChip />
      Icon Skeleton
      <SkeletonIcon size="medium" />
      Text Skeleton (4 lines)
      <SkeletonText numberOfLines={4} spacing={4} />
      Container Skeleton
      <SkeletonContainer className={styles.containerSkeleton} />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Code Example

```tsx
import React from 'react';
import { SkeletonAction } from '@ids-ts/skeleton';

const ExampleSkeleton = () => <SkeletonAction size="small" />;

export default ExampleSkeleton;
```

